A Main Roads accreditation certificate in Operate Truck Mounted Attenuator will be issued to those meeting the following pre-requisites:

• an Australian Qualification Framework compliant Statement of Attainment in the Resources and Infrastructure Industry Training Package Unit of Competency RIIRTM301E – Operate a truck or trailer mounted attenuator, or equivalent (or the replacement unit of competency if and when applicable);

• hold a current and valid heavy vehicle licence of a suitable class to operate the TMA (Medium Rigid licence as a minimum)

• hold a valid Work Safe WA Construction Induction Training card;

• hold a current Main Roads Basic Worksite Traffic Management Accreditation (see 8.3);

• documentary evidence of setting up at least 3 TTM sites in the last 12 months.
